            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-01-05T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-05-31T23:30:00-05:00" n="47" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d47">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The Iraq Petroleum Company completed a 16-inch pipeline to Tripoli, Lebanon,
                    presumably in the summer of 1949. The first flow of crude oil through the
                    pipeline reached the Mediterranean seaboard on or about July 9 (airgram 384,
                    August 10, from Beirut, 890G.6363/8–1049).</p>
            </div>
        </body>
